reviews.text: Love the brand, love the switch plate and outlet covers, BUT **not** the switches. Someone at the company had the idea of adding the brand to the front of the switches As a result, not only do you lose the clean look and feel of a Decora-style switch, embossed / debossed branding letters collect dirt. This is a big issue, and moreover they are not easy to clean. Very unfortunate; we searched everywhere for a place that carried clean Leviton switches but all seem to be branded now. 1. They collect dirt and grime 2. Not easy to clean once handled 3. No longer present a clean look 4. Do not match other switches on the property Posting this both to share our experience (marks were unexpected), and as a constructive comment -- hoping for a change in the future :)
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on June 27, 2023
reviews.title: We are OFF Leviton Switches

reviews.productTitle: Leviton 5691-2W 15 Amp, 120/277 Volt, Decora Plus Rocker Single-Pole AC Quiet Switch, Commercial Grade, White
reviews.text: Replaced a "residential grade" leviton switch with this commercial one. Construction is significantly better, however, it is far from quiet. It is a loud click, much louder than the residential one (which I would consider quiet). Per photo attached: Leviton Commercial switch click is 71.7 decibels, Leviton Residential is 60.3 decibels - at 8 inches away from switch. This 10db difference translates into 2 times louder! I double checked the product number 5691-2W and it matches the product listing. I bought two of these, and both are the same click volume. It's in a bedroom, which makes the click more annoying. Will likely end up returning these.
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on April 24, 2023
reviews.title: Not a quiet switch at all, twice as loud as residential version

Be sure you know what you are doing, and if not, either hire a licensed electrician or take the time to watch an instructional video on YouTube. KILL THE CIRCUIT AT THE BREAKER before opening up any electrical switch or outlet on that circuit!! Once open, test ALL the wiring for the presence of electricity. If you plan to do more that a couple of these kinds of jobs, buy the typical test equipment found here on Amazon (receptacle and non-contact voltage tester).

reviews.productTitle: Leviton 5691-2W 15 Amp, 120/277 Volt, Decora Plus Rocker Single-Pole AC Quiet Switch, Commercial Grade, White
reviews.text: OK - This is a typical, high-quality Leviton item, which we expect to last as long as the house. It mounts easy, looks great and is easy to use. Contrary to what we originally thought, this item is not lighted, but that's not critical for our application. The switch has a softer, quieter feature, which means it's silent when you turn it on or off. If you're used to a more positive click feel and sound from a light switch, this one is different. This is a typical SPST switch, but one downside is that it only accommodates one wire per connection. So for circuits with two feed wires, this means you will have to either double up on the screw terminal or use one push-in and the other wound on the screw. If they simply would've provided two push in connections for each terminal, it would've been much more convenient.
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on February 17, 2022
reviews.title: Nice, Affordable Switch
